    "slug": "hello-nextjs-16",
    "title": "Hello, Next.js 16",
    "excerpt": "Why Next.js 16's Cache Components change how we think about rendering.",
    "content": "Next.js 16 makes caching explicit. With Cache Components enabled, every page is dynamic by default and you opt specific work into the cache with the use cache directive.\n\nThis post itself is rendered from a cached read of a JSON file. Editing it in the admin invalidates the cache by tag, so you see your changes immediately.",
    "coverId": "1015",
    "author": "Ada Lovelace",
