    "id": "2",
    "slug": "the-proxy-boundary",
    "title": "The Proxy Boundary",
    "excerpt": "middleware.ts is now proxy.ts — and the admin area lives behind it.",
    "content": "In Next.js 16, middleware.ts becomes proxy.ts to make the network boundary explicit.\n\nIn this blog, the proxy guards every /admin route: without the admin-auth cookie you are redirected to the login page. It also redirects the legacy /blog/:slug URLs to /posts/:slug.",
    "coverId": "1025",
    "author": "Grace Hopper",
    "createdAt": "2026-02-02T14:30:00.000Z",
